OL,3,CRecord rainfall leaves 42 of farmer's
OL,4,C50 fields unusable
OL,6,FA farmer from North Lincolnshire says
OL,7,Fhis business is fighting for survival
OL,8,Fafter unprecedented rainfall ruined
OL,9,Fhis crops.
OL,11,FArable farmer Colin Chappell said his
OL,12,Fland in Brigg would normally be full
OL,13,Fof wheat, barley and peas, but he has
OL,14,Fonly been able to drill seeds in eight
OL,15,Fout of his 50 fields.
OL,17,FHe described the situation as
OL,18,F"horrendous" after a year's worth of
OL,19,Frain fell in the first four months of
OL,20,F2024.
