OL,3,CRecord rainfall leaves 42 of farmer's
OL,4,C50 fields unusable
OL,6,F"We haven't had more than five
OL,7,Fconsecutive days without rainfall
OL,8,Fsince 1 October," he said.
OL,10,F"There is a third of my farm which
OL,11,Fwill not grow a crop this year. For
OL,12,Fsix months I have been sat in my
OL,13,Foffice twiddling my thumbs. It has
OL,14,Fbeen horrible."
OL,16,FA report has found harvests across the
OL,17,Fcountry could be down by a fifth,
OL,18,Fwhich means prices for everyday items
OL,19,Flike, bread, beer and biscuits are
OL,20,Fbeing pushed up.
